
<p>
    In the unit on the <a href = '/unit/waves/wave_structure'>structure of a wave</a>,
    we learned all of the different <a href = '/pod/9ac868'>parts of a wave</a>.
    One of the most crucial parts of a wave is the wavelength.
    To understand the next major topic, harmonics,
    we need to understand wavelength in more depth.
    This pod deals with how to know a wavelength from a diagram of a wave and a measurement of distance.
</p>
<p>
    The <emph>wavelength</emph> is always the same distance for a wave,
    but it can be measured in four different ways.
</p>

